verses.roman:
keha paiḍa, keha nāḍu, keha piṭhā-pānā
bahu-mūlya uttama-prasāda-prakāra yāra nānā

synonyms: keha—someone; paiḍa—a coconut preparation; keha—someone; nāḍu—sweetballs; keha—someone; piṭhā—cakes; pānā—sweet rice; bahu-mūlya—costly; uttama-prasāda—very palatable food; prakāra yāra nānā—of different varieties.
translation: Some brought paiḍa [a coconut preparation], some brought sweetballs, and some brought cakes and sweet rice. The prasāda was of different varieties, all very costly.
